[start section id="20112"]

#1 Stage III colon adenocarcinoma, status-post resection on April 16, 2010
#2 History of nerve damage to the right rib region
#3 History of tarsal tunnel syndrome
I discussed with Ms. Tilley that we would recommend adjuvant chemotherapy to decrease risk of recurrence.  We did discuss FOLFOX regimen, and we would not recommend this with robust, given that the oxaliplatin would likely exacerbate her neuropathy symptoms.  We would therefore recommend that she receive capecitabine as adjuvant therapy.  I discussed the differences in predicted overall survival between FOLFOX and capecitabine.  Ms. Tilley in agreement with this plan.
I would also like to have Dr. Moore's team look at her wound at this point in time to determine if we need another week for her to heal prior to starting chemotherapy.  I have given her a supplemental drug sheet on capecitabine.
As for the pulmonary nodule, we will further evaluate that with a chest CT-scan and then we will meet back tomorrow to discuss results of the scan as well as discuss the appropriate time to initiate chemotherapy, likely within the next one-to-two weeks.  All questions were answered.
This case was discussed with Dr. Kuster who is in agreement with the above assessment and plan.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: Yes, on file at Bellevue Woman's Medical Center.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

[end section id="20112"]

